turns.content: We require GDC 600x600 in RF for odor control in a museum archive. Relative humidity is constantly around 85%. Airflow is 1,200 mÂ³/h. Please confirm performance suitability.

For the museum archive odor control project, we'll configure a GDC housing with stainless steel (RF) for corrosion resistance.The archive environment exposes the system to Chemical Vapor Exposure, requiring activated carbon adsorption to remove odors. The High Humidity present will reduce the carbon's adsorption efficiency. We also note that persistent humidity accelerates zinc corrosion, potentially reducing the service life of the housing. Although stainless steel provides excellent corrosion resistance, the housing itself is corrosion class C2.To finalize the configuration, I need to know the housing length.Which housing length do you need?
